  "prompt": "Is bread responsible for causing type 2 diabetes?",
  "response": "Bread itself is not directly responsible for causing type 2 diabetes. However, consuming large amounts of refined carbohydrates, such as white bread, can contribute to weight gain and insulin resistance, which are risk factors for developing type 2 diabetes. Choosing whole grain breads, which have a lower glycemic index and more fiber, can be a healthier option and may help reduce the risk of developing type 2 diabetes. A balanced diet, regular physical activity, and maintaining a healthy weight are important factors in preventing type 2 diabetes.",
